        "description": "Help the youth get acquainted as you check rooms for pre-session damage. This should take no more than 15 minutes. Damage report instructions are outlined below. Encourage the youth to leave their rooms and all areas of use in better condition than when they arrived.\n\nDamage Reports During room checks from 1:15 to 1:30 p.m., assess room conditions with this checklist:\n❏ Nonfunctioning or broken equipment (doors, locks, drawers, blinds, and so on)\n❏ Marks, scratches, or tape on walls, doors, or furniture\n❏ Window or screen damage (cracked, broken, torn, missing, and so on)\n❏ Stains on carpets or curtains\n❏ Broken keys\n❏ Damage to mirrors, towel racks, closets, sinks, and so on\n❏ Missing equipment (garbage cans, blinds, and so on)\n❏ Mattress or bedding damage (tears, slashes, and so on)\n❏ Damage to any other furniture (desks, chairs, and so on)\n❏ Immediately inform your AC when room checks have been completed, and report any pre-session damage in the app as instructed in training.\n\t• Report damage that must be addressed immediately (for example, a broken shower head, faucet, nonworking electrical outlets, and so on) to your AC.\n\t• Instruct the youth to immediately report to you any damage that occurs during the week.\n\nDURING THE WEEK\nReport midweek damage to your AC.",
