        "description": "Report head count information to AC.\nThis meeting is to excite the youth about the coming week, introduce the leadership team, and share crucial information for the upcoming activities. It can initiate company and session unity efforts.\n• Please wait for an AC to seat you and your company.\n• CNs should stay on their feet and be dancing to promote excitement, keeping an eye on the youth until the session coordinator stands up to get the meeting started.\n• You must sit on an aisle seat with your company and help the youth become enthused.\n• Don’t underestimate the power of your example! Cheer for everyone and everything, and the youth will begin to follow your example.\n• The CNs should learn the orientation dance and perform at orientation.\n• Before the end of orientation, have a plan with your co-CN for where you will meet during dinner, and communicate this information to your youth. Note: When seating for orientation (or any large group activity), some youth may need to use the restroom. Have them be seated first before going to the restroom, or make sure you save them seats so they can still sit with the company.",
