        "description": "Your company will prepare a banner and cheer for the cheer-off, meeting as early as 5:50 p.m. if desired.\n\n• You or your co-CN will get a banner kit during your afternoon AC meeting.\n• The banner and crayons will be used in other activities during the week—keep them.\n\nRules for the Banner\n• The banner must be appropriate and reflect the character of the company name.\n• CNs cannot draw on the banner.\n• Please do not use names, other than your company name or titles of Deity on your banner.\n\nRules for the Cheer\nYour company will prepare a cheer to present to the judges (usually the session adviser and SCs). The judges’ selections will perform at the cheer-off finals, the Taking It Home Showcase, or both. The rules below will ensure appropriateness, safety, and fairness.\n\n• Keep the cheer to around one minute.\n• Remember that judges look for enthusiasm, creativity, group unity, and overall performance.\n• CNs may not participate in the cheer but may encourage and help with ideas. The purpose is for the youth to work as a group and become more unified, not to win the competition. CNs are responsible for making sure the youth understand and comply with the expectations below.\n  • Flips and lifts are not permitted.\n  • With the exception of your banner, no props may be used.\n  • Do not use scriptural references or the names of Deity.\n  • Make sure tunes come from appropriate songs and that all cheer lyrics are appropriate.\n  • Profanity, vulgarity, and demeaning language of any kind is not permitted.",
