        "start": "19:00",
        "end": "19:15",
        "description": "Dances at FSY provide a wholesome social experience where the Spirit may be present. Youth are encouraged to learn new dances and practice social etiquette.\n\nAfter banner and cheer prep and before the dance begins, regroup with your company and review FSY Social Etiquette.\n\nIf you have extra time, you may want to teach your youth a line dance or some fun dance moves.\n\nFSY Social Etiquette\nGUIDELINES\n\nThroughout the Evening\n• Try to make more friends and get to know someone new!\n• Try out new dance moves—keep them appropriate!\n• Remember, FSY is not the place for romantic behavior.\n• Extra-mile tips:\n  • Don’t forget to smile!\n  • Variety makes dancing more fun!\n\nAvoid\n• Full-body contact (such as bear-hugging)\n• Positions or moves that are suggestive\n• Hanging out in the hall or restroom\n• Throwing objects or using glow sticks\n• Dancing that is potentially harmful to yourself or others, including flips, lifts, trains, moshing (jumping out of control), and so on\n\nWhat will you find at an FSY dance?\n• Popular, positive music\n• Great line dances\n• Lights on (so you can see all your friends and show off your moves)\n• Respectful peers\n• Tons of fun!",
