        "title": "Gospel Study",
        "start": "08:30",
        "end": "09:30",
        "description": "Follow day three gospel study as outlined below. Remember that being flexible in your teaching will provide an avenue for you to follow the Spirit and teach in ways that would be most effective for the youth in your company.\n\nSee Gospel Study Overview from Day Two.\n\nGospel study enables the youth to increase their love of the scriptures, learn how the scriptures can bless their lives, and develop a habit of daily study.\n\nRegular effective gospel study brings us closer to Jesus Christ and gives us power to resist temptation, avoid deception, and stay on the covenant path. Reading the scriptures invites the Spirit to be with us, helping us receive revelation, gain a testimony, and receive comfort. As we study, we learn doctrine that changes our actions and behavior.\n\nYour goal when leading gospel study should be to help the youth learn as you teach in the Savior’s way. As you do, the youth will give place in their hearts for the seed of the gospel to be planted, to swell, and to grow.\n\nObjectives:\n- Teach the youth methods to deepen their personal scripture study habits and understanding.\n- Help the youth recognize and learn by the Spirit.\n\nPreparation:\n- Gospel study provides each CN with a formal teaching opportunity. Prepare well. Your personal daily spiritual preparation is vital. Pray, study the scriptures, and be obedient. Your example will be more impressive than your words, so practice what you teach.\n- During co-counselor planning on the morning of day one, divide the daily teaching responsibilities and plan the scriptures you will be using during the week.\n- Read and use the online teaching skills.\n- Watch the video “Teaching the Gospel in the Savior’s Way.”\n\nTime Frame:\n- Formal teaching time—group discussion: 8:30–8:50 a.m.\n- Personal study time: 8:50–9:20 a.m.\n- Sharing time: 9:20–9:30 a.m.\n\nGospel Study Format:\nEach morning in your company spot, after singing and praying together, you and your co-CN should lead a short gospel study lesson to help the youth apply study skills. One CN teaches and the other CN supports with thoughtful comments and ideas. Help the youth gain an overall vision of how the gospel study lessons from the whole week tie together. Each day quickly review things that have been taught previously.\n\nThe best way for participants to apply these lessons is within their personal scripture study. Practice what you are teaching; study your scriptures, and do not meet with your co-CNs or do other things. Be observant and available to your youth during this time. Assist those who need help, have questions, or are distracted or sleeping. Be sensitive to the spiritual needs of your youth. After all have finished their personal study, invite the youth to share thoughts and feelings with one another. Remind them to share the gospel principles they learned, what they felt, and what study skill they applied, rather than just what they read.",
