        "start": "18:45",
        "end": "20:00",
        "description": "Objectives:\nHelp the youth:\n- Become united as a company.\n- Feel the Spirit while having fun.\n- Step outside comfort zones.\n\nPreparation:\nInvite your youth to practice their cheer and finish the banner, and then help them understand the games before Wednesday night.\n\nInstructions:\nThe participants will follow the example and leadership of the counselors during games night. Help the atmosphere to be one of encouragement, excitement, and teamwork and not one of disunity and competition. Remember that the purpose of games night is to help unify your company. Help your youth have fun in a way that doesn’t bring unnecessary attention to you and that is uplifting to the other companies. Extra attire for games night should be limited to a pair of sunglasses or a hat.\n\nArrive at the game field on time and check in with the assistant coordinator in charge. They will tell you which game you will play first and where to start your rotation. Be familiar with the game descriptions so you can explain them quickly and clearly to your company. Remind your youth to be familiar with them as well.\n\nYour group will rotate activities throughout the night until you have participated in each game.\n\nIf you have extra time between rotations, be ready to keep your company together, active, and excited. Cheering for other teams, practicing line dances, or preparing for other games are all acceptable activities. Also, please make sure your participants stay hydrated. When leaving your games night location, make sure youth have collected all belongings.\n\nNote:\nIf you have youth who suffer from anxiety, you may want to prepare them ahead of time for the environment and energy of games night. Make a plan for them to participate in ways that can stretch their comfort zone a little while they still feel safe. If you have any youth with physical disabilities, plan with them ahead of time for ways they can participate.\n\nGames:\n- Crazy Zoo Relay.\n- Dragon and Shield.\n- A House of Order.\n- Secret Dancer.\n- Captain’s Orders (Alternative Game).\n\nCheer-Off:\nAfter watching all the cheers during games night, the session coordinators and session adviser will choose a few cheers to be performed for the whole session in the final Cheer-Off. This is a time to be with your youth, have fun, and cheer on other groups. Encourage your youth to always be positive and supportive. There should be no booing or negative comments. If your group does not win, be cheerful; your example will determine the attitude of the youth.",
