        "description": "Slide Show:\nPreparation—During the Week:\nTake pictures of your youth throughout the week’s activities, and send the pictures to the AC assigned to the slide show. The youth may be disappointed if they do not see themselves or other members of their company in the slide show.\n\nTaking It Home Showcase:\nObjectives:\nReview and celebrate the week, highlighting ways the youth can take home something from each activity.\n\nPreparation:\n• Remind the youth all week to be pondering how they can “take home” principles from each activity.\n• Encourage them to respond to the questions that are posted on Instagram so that their answers might be featured in the Taking It Home Showcase on day five.\n• Encourage the youth to post uplifting and interesting things throughout the week and tag the team account. Remind them that they can submit art, poetry, and so on to possibly be featured in the showcase.\n• Make sure your youth are using the correct session hashtag and are tagging the team Instagram account.\n• Get your youth excited to recap the week and discuss how they can take it home.\n\nInstructions:\nAs a CN, when you are engaged and encouraging, the youth will mirror your excitement. If you are distracted and do not participate, your youth will not become readily involved on their own. The Taking It Home Showcase requires lots of involvement from the CNs during the activity to be successful.\n\n• Encourage your youth to cheer on the performances and be involved in the audience-participation segments.\n• For Kahoot, help your youth who do not have smartphones by submitting votes for those youth. Youth who don’t have smartphones could also partner with neighbors who have phones to answer trivia questions.\n• Help youth remember that the competition is just for fun, and winning is not the ultimate goal.",
