        "description": "The session adviser facilitates this activity. Sit with your youth and encourage them to take notes and participate. Prepare to help the youth create goals at Company Taking It Home based on the Do and Become invitation (page 136) and Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth (pages 35–36, 134).\n\nTaking It Home—Connecting the Dots:\nTaking It Home is divided into four parts. Each part is important, and each builds on the last.\n\nPart 1: Home Evening Goal-Setting:\nThe counselors use this activity to unify the company by laying a foundation for goal-setting as outlined in Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth.\n\nPart 2: Goal-Setting Review:\nCounselors will help the youth recognize the impact setting goals has on their lives and encourage them to continue setting goals after they go home.\n\nPart 3: Taking It Home Message:\nThe session adviser will reflect on the week and review morning devotional topics as well as extend the “Do and Become” invitation.\n\nPart 4: Company Taking It Home:\nCounselors will discuss the “it” in “Taking It Home” by connecting the principles shared during Taking It Home, including the “Do and Become” invitation. Help the youth to set and share goals, and teach the importance of using Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth as they set goals.",
