        "title": "Company Taking It Home",
        "start": "21:00",
        "end": "21:30",
        "description": "Objectives:\nHelp the youth:\n• Understand that the “it” in “Taking It Home” refers to the gospel principles they have learned and lived at FSY.\n• Set personal goals to live the gospel using the FSY “Do and Become” invitation and focus on steps from Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth.\n• Strengthen their conviction to continually use “A Pattern for Growth” by discovering, planning, acting, and reflecting on their goals.\n• Mention the JustServe app and the Book of Mormon app as ways to help share the gospel.\n\nResponsibilities:\n• Discuss the “it” in “Taking It Home.”\n• Review the Do and Become invitation extended by the session adviser.\n• Teach the youth that as they consistently apply what they have learned at FSY, their goals will become more meaningful and have greater significance.\n• Reinforce the goal-setting principles taught using “A Pattern for Growth.”\n• Facilitate a discussion that allows the youth to set and share goals.\n\nTime Frame:\nCompany Taking It Home discussion: 9:00–9:10 p.m.\nGoal setting: 9:10–9:15 p.m.\nGoal sharing: 9:15–9:25 p.m.\nWrap-up: 9:25–9:30 p.m.\n\nCompany Taking It Home Format\n\nDiscussion (7–10 minutes):\n• Connect the principles shared by the session adviser in the Taking It Home message and “Do and Become” invitation to the “it” that is being taken home. Help the youth understand that applying gospel principles throughout their lives will help them become more like the Savior.\n• Review the pattern for growth from Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth. Help youth realize that setting and achieving goals will help them find balance in their life. This pattern of living will anchor them to the gospel and help them continue to make and keep sacred covenants and attain celestial glory.\n\nGoal-Setting (5 minutes):\nEmphasize the importance of using Youth Guidebook: A Pattern for Growth to set goals:\n• Discover what you need to work on.\n• Plan how you will do it.\n• Act on your plan in faith.\n• Reflect on what you have learned.\n• Celebrate what you have accomplished.\n\nGive youth time to ponder and write personal goals they would like to accomplish when they return home. Encourage them to review and use the notes they have recorded each day during Reflect and Review. They can also consider the invitations offered in the Do and Become invitation.\n\nGoal Sharing (10–15 minutes):\nGive your youth the opportunity to share their goals, and let them explain how they will accomplish them. The youth can have a powerful influence on each other as they learn together and strengthen their determination to achieve their goals. Remind the youth of the following do’s and don’ts.\n\nDo:\n• Share goals that uplift one another.\n• Keep your comments brief so you give others time to share.\n• Show support for others as they share their goals.\n\nDon’t:\n• Share goals that are too personal or that involve serious sins.\n• Be critical of another’s goals.\n• Use this time to talk about friends or family; use this time to focus on what YOU will do when you return home.\n\nWrap-up (2–3 minutes):\nConclude this activity by joining your co-CNs in briefly sharing your testimonies with the youth. Set an example by following the principles you taught during the Reverence—Testimony Discussion.",
